                <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-md">
                  <button
                    type="button"
                    class="faq-question w-full flex justify-between items-center px-4 py-3 text-left"
                  >
                    <span class="font-medium text-sm"
                      >What is the difference between marginal and effective tax
                      rate?</span
                    >
                    <span class="ml-2 text-gray-500">+</span>
                  </button>
                  <div
                    class="faq-answer px-4 pb-3 text-sm text-gray-700 hidden"
                  >
                    Your marginal tax rate is the rate applied to your last
                    dollar of income (the highest bracket you reach). Your
                    effective tax rate is your total tax divided by your total
                    income. Because lower brackets apply to the first slices of
                    income, your effective rate is usually much lower than your
                    top marginal rate.
                  </div>
